  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" N.P. Saseendran versus N.P. Ponnamma & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_3_957_1010','2025INSC388'); ><font size='4'> <strong>N.P. SASEENDRAN<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>N.P. PONNAMMA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 3 S.C.R. 957</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 388</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004392025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The question to be decided herein is twin fold, whether the document of the year 1985 is a gift or Settlement or Will and whether the requirements under law or conditions in the deed have been satisfied to vest a legal right. Headnotes&dagger; Transfer of Property Act, Indian Stamp Act, 1899 &ndash; Art. 33 &ndash; Kerala Stamp Act, 1959 &ndash; Art.31 &ndash; Registration Act, 1909 &ndash; s.17 &ndash; Specific Relief Act, 1963 &ndash; s.2(b) &ndash; Indian Succession Act, 1925 &ndash; Part VI &ndash; ss.2(h), 59, 61, 62, 63, 70, 89 &ndash; Respondent No.1 was<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 24-03-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 4312/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_3_957_1010','2025INSC388','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class=